comments: Love how the cardio stays consistent throughout the workout. Exactly what I’ve been looking for.
I'm a 30+ year gym rat and ex-pro athlete. During covid I got fat and depressed and quit. This was my first workout in years, and the simplicity of it is pure gold. Thank you!

Madfit is indeed the best. I'm on my period and don't have much energy. After finishing this quick 10-min workout I suddenly want to do more 😂
Edit: I ended up doing another two 10-min workouts. That's 30minutes today! This is the habit -- just start small and once you're fired up, do more and keep going.
No idea if I'll ever be able to do it at such a high pace, but I did it at my own pace and I'm proud! Thank you!

Just completed this, love that it's easy, requires no equipment,  and takes into consideration those of us like myself,  who live in an apartment and need exercises that don't cause noise to tenants below us. Thank you for this and please post more apartment friendly, zero equipment videos like this, love it!❤
